        <!-- Introduction Section -->
        <div class="mt-16 prose prose-indigo max-w-none">
            <h2>Introduction</h2>
            <p class="lead">
                ErrorLogDashboard is a powerful, real-time error tracking platform designed to help developers monitor and debug their applications efficiently.
            </p>

            <h3>Key Features</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Real-time Error Tracking</strong> - Errors appear in your dashboard instantly</li>
                <li><strong>Multi-Language Support</strong> - Works with any programming language or framework</li>
                <li><strong>Secure API</strong> - Protected with API keys and security headers</li>
                <li><strong>Stack Traces</strong> - Full stack trace capture for easy debugging</li>
                <li><strong>Team Collaboration</strong> - Share dashboards with your team</li>
                <li><strong>Flexible Plans</strong> - From free tier to enterprise solutions</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>How It Works</h3>
            <ol>
                <li><strong>Create a Project</strong> - Set up a new project in your dashboard</li>
                <li><strong>Get Your Keys</strong> - Receive an API key and security key</li>
                <li><strong>Integrate</strong> - Add a few lines of code to your application</li>
                <li><strong>Monitor</strong> - Watch errors appear in real-time on your dashboard</li>
            </ol>

            <h3>API Overview</h3>
            <p>
                Our API is simple and RESTful. All errors are sent via HTTP POST to your unique webhook URL.
                Each request must include your security key in the <code>X-Security-Key</code> header.
            </p>

            <div class="bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded-md">
                <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-700 mb-2">Example Request</p>
                <pre class="text-sm"><code>POST https://your-domain.com/api/ingest/{your-api-key}
Content-Type: application/json
X-Security-Key: {your-security-key}

{
  "message": "An error occurred",
  "stackTrace": "at MyApp.Program.Main() in Program.cs:line 42"
}</code></pre>
            </div>
